All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Map<Key, LinkedDateTimeTripletMap.LinkedTriplet>, SequencedMap<Key, LinkedDateTimeTripletMap.LinkedTriplet>
public class LinkedDateTimeTripletMap<Key> extends LinkedHashMap<Key, LinkedDateTimeTripletMap.LinkedTriplet>
This class is used as a parallel data-structure over the existing linked-map. To create the instance of that class - use any of factory-methods like create(SequencedMap, Function), createByEpochSeconds(SequencedMap, Function) or createByEpochSecondsInt(SequencedMap, Function)

    • create

      public static <Key,Value> LinkedDateTimeTripletMap<Key> create(SequencedMap<Key,Value> originalMap, Function<Value,Instant> instantFunc)
      Builds a chronological sequence of LinkedDateTimeTripletMap.LinkedTriplets over the original sequence map, where the passed instantFunc is used to extract that date-time chronological property
      Type Parameters:
      Key - a type of original map's key
      Value - a type of original map's value
      Parameters:
      originalMap - an original map over any values that has chronological property
      instantFunc - a reference to getter that is used to extract that date-time chronological property
      Returns:
      the linked-map with the same keys and sequence, but with LinkedDateTimeTripletMap.LinkedTriplet as value
